<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="337" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Insect almost circular, overall dorsal body color brown completely surrounded by a large impunctate shiny orange margin (
<figureCitation box="[546,614,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1709,1731]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,187,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1388,183,1684]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: Calagasma margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. Dorsal view drawn by Bergroth (1914). Scale = 2 mm. B: Epipedus histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil. Lectotype ♀ conserved at MRSN, dorsal view drawn by Rolston (1987), montage of his 3 separate figures (dorsal view, pronotum and right corium). Stippled areas correspond to a rufous (red-brown) color. Scale = 2 mm. C: E. histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil, Rio de Janeiro (Corcovado mountain) 1961, Alvarenga &amp; Seabra leg. ♀ specimen conserved at UFPR, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. D: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. syntype ♂ conserved at MZHF, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Pekka Malinen (MZHF), 2016. E: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana, Roura (Montagne des Chevaux RN 2 pK 22) 26. VII. 2014, SEAG leg. ♂ specimen, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Collection Roland Lupoli. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2015. F: same in partial lateral view. G: Epipedus rolstoni Lupoli, sp. nov. holotype ♀ conserved at AMNH, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. H: Calagasma eclipsa Lupoli, sp. nov. French Guiana, 1913 Dr Bongrand leg. holotype ♂ conserved at MNHN, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2016. I: same in ventral view. J: same in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260744/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
H). Head entirely shiny orange and impunctate including clypeus and vertex. Eyes brown. Clypeus shorter than mandibular plates. Mandibular plates parallel along lateral margins. Anterolateral margins of the pronotum shiny orange, impunctate and slightly concave. Callus raised upward (
<figureCitation box="[159,224,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1709,1731]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,187,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1388,183,1684]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: Calagasma margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. Dorsal view drawn by Bergroth (1914). Scale = 2 mm. B: Epipedus histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil. Lectotype ♀ conserved at MRSN, dorsal view drawn by Rolston (1987), montage of his 3 separate figures (dorsal view, pronotum and right corium). Stippled areas correspond to a rufous (red-brown) color. Scale = 2 mm. C: E. histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil, Rio de Janeiro (Corcovado mountain) 1961, Alvarenga &amp; Seabra leg. ♀ specimen conserved at UFPR, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. D: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. syntype ♂ conserved at MZHF, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Pekka Malinen (MZHF), 2016. E: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana, Roura (Montagne des Chevaux RN 2 pK 22) 26. VII. 2014, SEAG leg. ♂ specimen, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Collection Roland Lupoli. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2015. F: same in partial lateral view. G: Epipedus rolstoni Lupoli, sp. nov. holotype ♀ conserved at AMNH, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. H: Calagasma eclipsa Lupoli, sp. nov. French Guiana, 1913 Dr Bongrand leg. holotype ♂ conserved at MNHN, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2016. I: same in ventral view. J: same in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260744/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
J). Elsewhere, pronotum shiny brown with uniformly distributed deep concolorous dense punctation. Scutellum flat, completely shiny brown with deep concolorous dense punctation uniformly distributed, similarly to the shiny brown part of the pronotum. Corium mostly matt greenish brown, appearing similar to leather, with concolorous shallow punctation distributed in lines parallel to the wing veins. Apical half of exocorium shiny orange and impunctate. Anterolateral shiny orange border of exocorium strongly elevated (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1294,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1709,1731]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,187,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1388,183,1684]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: Calagasma margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. Dorsal view drawn by Bergroth (1914). Scale = 2 mm. B: Epipedus histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil. Lectotype ♀ conserved at MRSN, dorsal view drawn by Rolston (1987), montage of his 3 separate figures (dorsal view, pronotum and right corium). Stippled areas correspond to a rufous (red-brown) color. Scale = 2 mm. C: E. histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil, Rio de Janeiro (Corcovado mountain) 1961, Alvarenga &amp; Seabra leg. ♀ specimen conserved at UFPR, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. D: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. syntype ♂ conserved at MZHF, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Pekka Malinen (MZHF), 2016. E: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana, Roura (Montagne des Chevaux RN 2 pK 22) 26. VII. 2014, SEAG leg. ♂ specimen, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Collection Roland Lupoli. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2015. F: same in partial lateral view. G: Epipedus rolstoni Lupoli, sp. nov. holotype ♀ conserved at AMNH, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. H: Calagasma eclipsa Lupoli, sp. nov. French Guiana, 1913 Dr Bongrand leg. holotype ♂ conserved at MNHN, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2016. I: same in ventral view. J: same in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260744/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
J). Posterior margin of corium not sigmoid but almost linear, the costal angle forming a rounded corner. Connexivum shiny orange, impunctate, broadly exposed, as broadly as the exocorium. Venter brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1284,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1709,1731]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,187,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1388,183,1684]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: Calagasma margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. Dorsal view drawn by Bergroth (1914). Scale = 2 mm. B: Epipedus histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil. Lectotype ♀ conserved at MRSN, dorsal view drawn by Rolston (1987), montage of his 3 separate figures (dorsal view, pronotum and right corium). Stippled areas correspond to a rufous (red-brown) color. Scale = 2 mm. C: E. histrio Spinola, 1837. Brazil, Rio de Janeiro (Corcovado mountain) 1961, Alvarenga &amp; Seabra leg. ♀ specimen conserved at UFPR, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. D: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana. syntype ♂ conserved at MZHF, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Pekka Malinen (MZHF), 2016. E: C. margarita Bergroth, 1914. French Guiana, Roura (Montagne des Chevaux RN 2 pK 22) 26. VII. 2014, SEAG leg. ♂ specimen, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Collection Roland Lupoli. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2015. F: same in partial lateral view. G: Epipedus rolstoni Lupoli, sp. nov. holotype ♀ conserved at AMNH, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Jocelia Grazia, 2016. H: Calagasma eclipsa Lupoli, sp. nov. French Guiana, 1913 Dr Bongrand leg. holotype ♂ conserved at MNHN, dorsal view. Scale = 2 mm. Photo Roland Lupoli, 2016. I: same in ventral view. J: same in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260744/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">
Fig. 
<date box="[1273,1284,584,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">1</date>
</figureCitation>
I) as the legs (only the posterior right leg and right metafemur remain). Tibiae cylindrical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">
Pygophore thick, sclerotized and dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[717,785,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1733,1755]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,919,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,913,1711]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Calagasma eclipsa Lupoli, sp. nov. French Guiana, 1913 Dr. Bongrand leg. holotype ♂ conserved at MNHN. A: ♂ pygophore, dorsal view, B: idem ventral view, C: idem lateral view. Scales = 0.1 mm. Photos Roland Lupoli, 2016. Drdorsal rim; Vr—ventral rim; Pyg—pygophore; Pla—posterolateral angle; Pa—paramere; Pr—Proctiger or abdominal segment X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/260747/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="337">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A, B, C). Parameres and proctiger dark brown. Dorsal rim U-shaped leaving apparent, in the dorsal view, proctiger and parameres. Ventral rim thick, strong and almost straight in the ventral view. Posterolateral angles of pygophore very thick, ear-shaped, sclerotized, with short setae. Parameres flat and curved, postero-ventrally directed, positioned on their edge and parallel to each other. Ventral apices of the parameres reaching ventral rim and come to rest on it, apices shaped like small hands wearing tiny mittens. Proctiger cylindrical. Brown bilobed shape process located just behind the proctiger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
